  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your wok or pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Chop the onion and garlic finely; mince the ginger.",
    "Heat peanut oil in the wok, then add sliced onions and cook until soft.",
    "Add minced garlic and ginger, stir-fry for 30 seconds, followed by red pepper flakes.",
    "Stir in the soy sauce, rice vinegar, sesame oil, salt, and chili sauce. Bring to a simmer.",
    "Gently fold in potato rolls (ensure not overcooking).",
    "Toss with peanuts until heated through.",
    "Serve hot as an appetizer or light meal."
